oacSHDSLMIBModule.name: oacSHDSLMIBModule

revisions.description: This MIB module describes private extensions to the RFC4319 MIB.

oacSHDSLSpanStatusTable.name: oacSHDSLSpanStatusTable
oacSHDSLSpanStatusTable.description: This table provides overall status information of HDSL2/SHDSL spans. This table contains live data from equipment. As such, it is NOT persistent.

oacSHDSLSpanStatusEntry.name: oacSHDSLSpanStatusEntry
oacSHDSLSpanStatusEntry.description: An entry in the oacSHDSLSpanStatusTable. Each entry represents the complete span in a single HDSL2/SHDSL line. It is indexed by the ifIndex of the associated HDSL2/SHDSL line.

oacSHDSLSpanStatusUpDown.name: oacSHDSLSpanStatusUpDown
oacSHDSLSpanStatusUpDown.description: Contains the Global Up/Down Counter for the span.

oacSHDSLSpanStatusCurrCellDelin.name: oacSHDSLSpanStatusCurrCellDelin
oacSHDSLSpanStatusCurrCellDelin.description: Contains the current Cell Delin counter.

oacSHDSLSpanStatusCurrRxCells.name: oacSHDSLSpanStatusCurrRxCells
oacSHDSLSpanStatusCurrRxCells.description: Contains the current Rx Cells counter.

oacSHDSLSpanStatusCurrTxCells.name: oacSHDSLSpanStatusCurrTxCells
oacSHDSLSpanStatusCurrTxCells.description: Contains the current Tx Cells counter.

oacSHDSLSpanStatusCurrRxDrops.name: oacSHDSLSpanStatusCurrRxDrops
oacSHDSLSpanStatusCurrRxDrops.description: Contains the current Rx Drops counter.

oacSHDSLSpanStatusCurrConstellation.name: oacSHDSLSpanStatusCurrConstellation
oacSHDSLSpanStatusCurrConstellation.description: The current constellation (line coding) for the span.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrTable.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrTable
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrTable.description: This table contains current status and performance information for segment endpoints in HDSL2/SHDSL lines. As with other tables in this MIB module indexed by ifIndex, entries in this table MUST be maintained in a persistent manner.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrEntry.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrEntry
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrEntry.description: Defines an entry in the oacSHDSLEndpointCurrTable.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrAtn.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrAtn
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrAtn.description: The current loop attenuation for this endpoint as reported in a Network or Customer Side Performance Status message. In tenths of dB.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrSnrMgn.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrSnrMgn
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrSnrMgn.description: The current SNR margin for this endpoint as reported in a Status Response/SNR message. In tenths of dB.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrTxPwr.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrTxPwr
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrTxPwr.description: The current transmit power for this endpoint. In tenths of dB.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrRxGain.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrRxGain
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrRxGain.description: The current receiver gain for this endpoint. In tenths of dB.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrMaxAttainableLineRat.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrMaxAttainableLineRate
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrMaxAttainableLineRat.description: The current Max Attainable LineRate for this endpoint.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrCommands.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrCommands
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrCommands.description: The current Commands for this endpoint.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrResponses.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrResponses
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrResponses.description: The current Responses for this endpoint.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrdiscardedCommands.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrdiscardedCommands
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrdiscardedCommands.description: The current discarded Commands for this endpoint.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrerroredCommands.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrerroredCommands
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrerroredCommands.description: The current errored Commands for this endpoint.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrReceivedFrames.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrReceivedFrames
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrReceivedFrames.description: The current Received Frames for this endpoint.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrBadTransparency.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrBadTransparency
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrBadTransparency.description: The current Bad Transparency for this endpoint.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrBadFCS.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrBadFCS
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrBadFCS.description: The current Bad FCS for this endpoint.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrEOCStatus.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrEOCStatus
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrEOCStatus.description: The current EOC Status for this endpoint.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainTable.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainTable
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainTable.description: This table contains current status and performance information for segment endpoints in HDSL2/SHDSL lines. As with other tables in this MIB module indexed by ifIndex, entries in this table MUST be maintained in a persistent manner.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainEntry.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainEntry
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainEntry.description: Defines an entry in the oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainTable.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainSQPAIR.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainSQPAIR
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainSQPAIR.description: The current retrain SQ for this endpoint as reported in a Network or Customer Side Performance Status message.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainSQLINE.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainSQLINE
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainSQLINE.description: The current retrain SQ for this endpoint as reported in a Network or Customer Side Performance Status message.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainCRCPAIR.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainCRCPAIR
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainCRCPAIR.description: The current retrain CRC for this endpoint as reported in a Network or Customer Side Performance Status message.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainCRCLINE.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainCRCLINE
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainCRCLINE.description: The current retrain CRC for this endpoint as reported in a Network or Customer Side Performance Status message.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainFsyncPAIR.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainFsyncPAIR
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainFsyncPAIR.description: The current retrain Fsync for this endpoint as reported in a Network or Customer Side Performance Status message.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainFsyncLINE.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainFsyncLINE
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainFsyncLINE.description: The current retrain Fsync for this endpoint as reported in a Network or Customer Side Performance Status message.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainFSyncSQPAIR.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainFSyncSQPAIR
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainFSyncSQPAIR.description: The current retrain FSync&SQ for this endpoint as reported in a Network or Customer Side Performance Status message.

oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainFSyncSQLINE.name: oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainFSyncSQLINE
oacSHDSLEndpointCurrretrainFSyncSQLINE.description: The current retrain FSync&SQ for this endpoint as reported in a Network or Customer Side Performance Status message.

oacSHDSLHardDownTrap.name: oacSHDSLHardDownTrap
oacSHDSLHardDownTrap.description: this notification indicate that the shdsl line speed is lower than the threshold configured in efm interface. as consequence, the interface ethernet which the hard-down option is enable will be shutdown, it will be UP if the shdsl line recovered the good linerate.

oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileTable.name: oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileTable
oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileTable.description: This table supports definitions of span configuration profiles for SHDSL lines. This table MUST be maintained in a persistent manner

oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileEntry.name: oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileEntry
oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to a single span configuration profile. Each profile contains a set of span configuration parameters. The configuration parameters in a profile are applied to those lines referencing that profile (see the hdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfile object).

oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileConstellation.name: oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileConstellation
oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileConstellation.description: The configured constellation (line coding) for the span. Corresponds to cli command (controller shdsl 0, dsl-group 0): annex ... tc-pam <value>

oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileAutoConfig.name: oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileAutoConfig
oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileAutoConfig.description: The configured auto configuration mode (enabled or disabled) for the span. Corresponds to cli command (controller shdsl 0, dsl-group 0): autoconfig / no autoconfig

oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileCaplist.name: oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileCaplist
oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileCaplist.description: The configured capability list style for the span. Corresponds to cli command (controller shdsl 0, dsl-group 0): caplist <value>

oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileEfmAggregation.name: oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileEfmAggregation
oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileEfmAggregation.description: The configured efm aggregation mode for the span. Corresponds to cli command (controller shdsl 0, dsl-group 0): efmaggregation <value>

oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileCrcCheck.name: oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileCrcCheck
oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileCrcCheck.description: The configured numbered of consecutive seconds with crc errors after which the link will be retrained. If the value is set to 0, than no retrain will occur based on crc errors. Corresponds to cli command (controller shdsl 0, dsl-group 0): value 0 : crc no all other values: crc check <value>

oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileMeansqCheck.name: oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileMeansqCheck
oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileMeansqCheck.description: The configured numbered of consecutive seconds where the noise margin is below the configured threshold (oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileMeansqThreshold) after which the link will be retrained. If the value is set to 0, than no retrain will occur based on noise margin verification. Corresponds to cli command (controller shdsl 0, dsl-group 0): value 0 : meansq no all other values: meansq check <value>

oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileMeansqThreshold.name: oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileMeansqThreshold
oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileMeansqThreshold.description: The configured threshold (in dB) for retrain check based on the noise margin. If the noise margin drops below the configured threshold for the configured time (oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileMeansqCheck) than the link will be retrained. Corresponds to cli command (controller shdsl 0, dsl-group 0): meansq check <time> <value>

oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileLineProbing.name: oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileLineProbing
oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileLineProbing.description: The configured linprobing mechanism. - normal corresponds to the standard line probing (pmms) as defined in the standard (G.991.2). - adaptive has to be used in situations where there is cross-talk between the lines of the same span. A propriatary algorithm will be activated that will limit the maximum speed if the normal line probing mechanism cannot reach a stable sync due to it's limitations (cross-talk is not taken into account in the standard line probing mechanism). The disadvantage of the adaptive mode is that it can take a long time before a stable sync is reached. Corresponds to cli command (controller shdsl 0, dsl-group 0): lineprobing <value>

oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileEocManagement.name: oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileEocManagement
oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileEocManagement.description: This object enables/disables the EOC management of the SHDSL line in this unit.

oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileEocStatusPollDela.name: oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileEocStatusPollDelay
oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileEocStatusPollDela.description: The delay in seconds after the start of the full quarter of an hour when an EOC full status request is sent to the devices in the span. Periodically after this start point full status request will be sent with a configured interval (oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileEocStatusPollInterval).

oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileEocStatusPollInte.name: oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileEocStatusPollInterval
oacSHDSLSpanConfProfileEocStatusPollInte.description: The delay in seconds between 2 EOC full status requests to the same device in the shdsl span.
